text:
Maria Thattil (born 1993 in Melbourne, Australia) is an Australian-Indian model, beauty expert, makeup artist, fashion stylist, fashion blogger, digital influencer and beauty pageant titleholder who was crowned Miss Universe Australia 2020.
Personal Life.
Thattil was born on 1993 in Melbourne to Indian parents who immigrated from India to Australia. On October 11, 2013, she graduated with honors from RMIT University in Melbourne with a bachelor’s degree in psychology. On November 17, 2017, she graduated from the University of Melbourne with a master’s degree in management.
Pageantry.
On October 28, 2020, Thattil was crowned Miss Universe Australia 2020 pageant and she will represent Australia at Miss Universe 2020.
